                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d597">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/9–544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-05T10:00:00+07:00"
                            >September 5, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10: 55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1502. Central News Agency despatch Tihwa, September 2, reports that General Chu
                    Shao-liang arrived in Tihwa August 31 and assumed post of acting Chairman of the
                    Sinkiang Provincial Government September 2; and that Sheng Shih-tsai is to leave
                    Tihwa shortly for Chungking to assume post of Minister of Agriculture and
                    Forestry.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
